        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 2 at 11:02PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 1102 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles north of Kenton, or 27 miles southwest of Springfield, moving
east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Campo and Stonington.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
